ENTRY            F1542   20260115   20260305   20260305       F106
SUBENT        F1542001   20260115   20260305   20260305       F106
BIB                 12         48
TITLE      Production of Th nuclei in the 48Ca+170Yb and
           54Cr+164Dy reactions
AUTHOR     (R.N.Sagaidak,V.K.Utyonkov,F.Sh.Abdullin,S.N.Dmitriev,
           D.Ibadullayev,M.G.Itkis,N.D.Kovrizhnykh,D.A.Kuznetsov,
           O.V.Petrushkin,A.V.Podshibiakin,A.N.Polyakov,
           A.G.Popeko,V.D.Shubin,M.V.Shumeiko,D.I.Solovyev,
           Yu.S.Tsyganov,A.A.Voinov,N.S.Bublikova,M.G.Voronyuk,
           A.V.Sabelnikov,A.Yu.Bodrov,Z.G.Gan,Z.Y.Zhang,
           M.H.Huang,H.B.Yang,X.Y.Huang)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,110,044609,2024)
           #doi:10.1103/PhysRevC.110.044609
INSTITUTE  (4ZZZDUB,4KASKAZ,3CPRIMP)
           (3CPRUCA) School of Nuclear Science and Technology
FACILITY   (CYCLO,4ZZZDUB) The DC280 cyclotron at the Superheavy
           Element Factory at JINR.
INC-SOURCE In target irradiation by the continuous 48Ca and 54Cr
           beams provided by cyclotron the beam intensity was
           limited to 1 p mu-A.
METHOD     (TOF,REC,ASPEC,BCINT)
DETECTOR   (MAGSP) Gas-filled separator (DGFRS-2) was used.
           (MWPC,SISD) DGFRS-2 was filled with hydrogen at a
           pressure of 0.9 Torr. A detector chamber was
           separated from the DGFRS-2 volume by a 0.7-micron
           Mylar foil and filled with pentane at a pressure of
           1.6 mbar. Pentane was a working gas for two multiwire
           proportional chambers (MWPCs) installed in front of
           the detector array to register particles arriving
           from the separator. The focal-plane detector array of
           48 mm in vertical and 220 mm in horizontal directions
           consisted of two 48x128 mm2 double-sided strip
           detectors, with 48 1-mm horizontal strips on the
           front side and 128 1-mm-wide vertical strips on the
           back one. The first detector shielded part of the
           rear detector. The back strips of 1 mm in width were
           paired together to form 110 strips of 2 mm in width.
           The focal detector was surrounded by eight 60x120 mm2
           side strip detectors, each with eight strips,
           constituting a box with a depth of 120 mm.
SAMPLE     Rotating target wheels, having six segments with the
           enriched 170Yb and 164Dy targets, were used in the
           experiments. Targets were prepared by electroplating
           onto 0.619+-0.007 mg/cm2 Ti backings.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) Uncertainties in the beam dose, target
           thickness, and evaporation residues transmission
           efficiency determinations were taken into account, in
           addition to the evident statistical errors.
STATUS     (TABLE,,R.N.Sagaidak+,J,PR/C,110,044609,2024) Table III
HISTORY    (20260115C)
ENDBIB              48
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           51
